I.  PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
This document specifies the procedures to be used for all Network
Host Interface Outages.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  DEFINITION
.skip 1
.left margin 18
Host Interface Outage.  The definition of a host or slot interface
outage is when the host or interface is unaccessable through the
Network, and is showing shut, down or missing.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III.  PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
This procedure needs the concurrent work of network control, field
engineering, customer service and the communications consultants.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  Network control is responsible for detecting host anomalies on
hosts which are normally answered 24 hours a day.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  Upon detection of an anomaly (down, shut or missing) network control
will make an evaluatin of the slot code and notify customer service.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
3.  For the purpose of reporting, network control will be responsible
for contacting field engineering and customer service will be responsible
for contacting communications consultants.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
4.  Network control will determine within means whether an anomaly
is hardware or software caused.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
5.  When a determination cannot be rendered, Field Engineering will
be contacted to have tthe line and modems tested.  Normal follow-up
will be used.
.page
.left margin 18
.indent -4
6.  If the line is tested okay and the anomaly has not been cleared
then the problem will be turned over to customer service.  A line
outage will then be handled by Netcon through a phone company.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
7.  Customer service will be responsible for getting a communicatin
consultant notified and working on the anomaly.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
8.  If a communicatin consultant feels that the transmission medium
is not functioning properly than software and hardware people will
work together as a team to correct the problem.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
9.  All line problems will be turned over to the phone companies
via network control.
