I.  PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
This document specifies the procedure to be used for moving the
Network Supervisor.  This procedure will be defined in two different
categories.  Scheduled moves and unscheduled moves.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  SCHEDULED MOVES
.skip 1
.left margin 18
A scheduled Supervisor move is when the active Network Supervisor
is put to sleep at a scheduled period of time, and access to the
Network is denied until another Network Supervisor is awakened, and
taken control of 75 percent of the Network (75 percent of the nodes
the Sup had last time active).
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  Prior to the actual move, make a copy of the ALL NODES List (AN), the
SHUT TABLE (LSHUT), and the COUNT OF MACHINES (COUNT)>
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  On the active Supervisor, do TSLEEP, enter the PASSWORD, but do not
do a carriage return at this time.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
3.  On the sleeping Supervisor, you are moving to, do a TWAKE, enter
the Password, but do not do a carriage return.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
4.  You are now set to do the actual Supervisor move.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
A.  Hit a carriage return on the active Supervisor.  You will get the
time the Supervisor went to sleep.  (024:ll:00:38)
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
B.  Ten seconds after sleeping the active supervisor, hit a carriage
return on the sleeping Supervisor  you wish to take over the Net.  You'll
get the time the Supervisor was awakened.
.page
