I.  Purpose
.skip 1
.left margin 10
This document specifies the procedures to be used for all SYNC DIAL BACK-UP 
HOST.
.skip 1
.indent -5
II.  Procedure
.skip 1
.left margin 10
When Network Control detects a SYNC DIAL BACK-UP HOST has gone shut via TMCS
or by phone notification.  The following steps must be taken.
.skip 1
.left margin 16
.indent -4
1.  Notify the customer that their Host interface has gone shut and you would
like for them to verify the following equipment as working.
.skip 1
.left margin 20
.indent -4
A.  Host interface:  Verify that the host is running code and shows no apparent
problems.
.skip 1
.left margin 20
.indent -4
B.  Modem:  Have the customer check for a loss of carrier.  The following
lights should be on RD, SD and RR.
.skip 1
.left margin 10
Note*  It is the customers option to use SYNC DIAL BACK-UP.
.skip 1
.left margin 10
.indent -4
2.  Once it has been determined that there is a line problem and the customer
wishes to use SYNC DIAL BACK-UP, do the following.
.skip 1
.left margin 20
.indent -4
1.  Have customer check DDD2 for dial tone.
.skip 1
1a.  Customer dials DDD2 to DDD1.
.skip 1
2.  Customer listens to line for click.
.skip 1
.left margin 20
Note*  This indicates the far end has answered.
.skip 1
.left margin 20
.indent -4
3,  Customer listens for static and X-talk/if present redial DDD2 to DDD1.
.skip 1
.left margin 20
.indent -4
4.  After click put line on hold.
.skip 1
.left margin 20
.indent -4
5.  Repeat process for DDD1 to DDD2.
.skip 1
.left margin 20
.indent -4
6.  Customer checks for:
.nofill
.nojustify
.left margin 45
RR  (carrier)
.left margin 45
RS  (request to send)
.left margin 45
CS  (clear to send)
.left margin 45
RD  (receive data)
.left margin 45
SD  (send data)
.left margin 45
BU  (back-up light on Sync. Dial back-up unit).
.fill
.justify
