II.  DEFINITION
.skip 1
.left margin 18
End of shift project summary.  The end of shift project summary is a detailed
status report of all projects on a daily basis which have been executed on
a specific shift, and are either completed or incomplete.  Projects
pending notification from various maintenance groups in which network
control has yet to be notified via telephone or Ontyme, will be labled
inprogress, by the off going shift.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III.  PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
At the end of each shift, network control staff is required to publish
a report via Ontyme called the End of Shift Project Summary.  This report
should be concise on all projects attempted, as well as completed for
that shift.  The report should be generated on Ontyme and sent out to
*projects.  Hardcopies on the project summary should be attached to
the shift turnover report for that specific shift, as well as one on the
project clip board.
