ON-CALL SOFTWARE SUPPORT
.BREAK
.SKIP 3

The following procedure describes the manner in which NETCON or NETAPS can
contact the on-call HQ Technical Support person for assistance on a software
problem.
.skip 2
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  If NETCON or NETAPS receives a call reporting a software problem, the
calling party is asked if the problem concerns:
.skip 1
a.  OnTyme; Outdial; or Railtrack, OR
.skip 1
b.  A Public Network customer, OR
.skip 1
c.  A Private Network
.skip 1
.indent -4
2.  If the call concerns OnTyme, Outdial, or Railtrack, it is directed to
NETCON and NETCON enters 408-262-8746; 1000 to contact the on-call person
supporting these applications.
.skip 1
.indent -4
3.  If the call concerns the Public Network (with the exception of the
applications covered by #2, above), it is directed to NETCON and NETCON 
enters 408-262-8746; ESCL to contact that support person.
.skip 1
.indent -4
4.  If the call concerns a Private or Independent Network, it is directed
to NETAPS and NETAPS enters 408-262-8746; PNET to contact the on-call support
person.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
When making contact with the appropriate on-call individual, the controller
should send a message describing the problem and a contact phone number to
be called.  The on-call person must inform the controller that they have
received the message.
.skip 1
If there is no response within ten (10) minutes, NETCON should re-try the
number just dialed and re-send the message.  After an additional ten (10)
minutes has passed (20 minutes after the original call), NETCON or NETAPS,
as appropriate, should enter 408-262-8746; MGMT, and send the original message.
