.figure 5
.center 84
NETWORK CONTROL PROCEDURES
.break
.skip 2
.center 84
CIRCUIT TRACING
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.  PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
This procedure defines the process by which circuits are traced through
the Network.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  DEFINITION
.skip 1
.left margin 18
The TRACE command traces a circuit in Tymnet II from a specified host
and port on a specified node.  It also traces the Tymnet II portion
of a circuit that corsses from Tymnet I into Tymnet II.  The trace
informatin consists of a list of Tymnet II nodes the circuit passes
through.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III.  PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
Syntax:  TRACE tymnet II node #   Ntymnet I node# channel #
or       TRACE tymnet II node#    Hhost #   port#
.skip 1
.left margin 18
For use with the CHAN command (Section 2.1.5) to trace control circuits,
the syntax is:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
          TRACE active-supervisor-sport#-node#
.fill
.justify
.skip 1
.left margin 18
Description:  The TRACE command traces a circuit in Tymnet II from a
specified host and port on a specified node.  It also traces the Tymnet II
portion of a circuit that crosses from Tymnet I into Tymnet II.  The  trace
information consists of a list of Tymnet II nodes the circuit passes
through.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
Following is a sample command and response sequence tracing a circuit
ending on Tymnet II node 2005, host 125, and port 5:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
:TRACE 2005 H125 5
HOST 125 PORT 5 2005 2010 2017 NODE 1306 CHANNEL 27
.SKIP 1
.LEFT MARGIN 18
.fill
.justify
Note that the previous circuit traced in the example crossed into
Tymnet I.
.left margin 18
.skip 1
When tracing this same circuit starting from the Tymnet I portion,
PROBE types the Tymnet II node number TII (#) where # is the decimal
channel number used on the link from the Tymnet I node to the Tymnet II node.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
Example:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
:CT 1303
TII (27) 2005 1306 1326 1303 P19
.skip 1
.left margin 18
The syntax to trace the Tymnet II portion of the circuit is:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
TRACE tymnet II node #  Ntymnet I node#  channel#
.skip 1
.left margin 18
A sample command/response sequence is:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
:TRACE 2005 N1306 27
NODE 1306 CHANNEL 27 2017 2005 HOST 125 PORT 5
.fill
.justify
.skip 1
.left margin 18
NOTE:  The user should be aware that this command generates data
flow in the network and may have a slow response time.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
IV.  LIMITATION
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  There is only one trace buffer in the Supervisor.  This limits
one execution of the trace command until the buffer is cleared.  If you
get data back and it appears wrong, you may have someone elses command.
The issuance of trace command is sent to the logger in order to alert you of the
buffer uses.
